When Hazel Sharp, daughter of Mirror Lake’s longtime local detective, unexpectedly inherits her childhood home, she’s warily drawn back to the town—and people—she left behind almost a decade earlier. But Hazel’s not the only relic of the past to return: a drought has descended on the region, and as the water level in the lake drops, long-hidden secrets begin to emerge... including evidence that may help finally explain the mystery of her mother’s disappearance.', 'Hazel inherits her detective father''s home in small-town Mirror Lake and returns after years away, unearthing family secrets tied to her mother''s abandonment and a deadly past.', 2024, NULL, '9781668010457', 368, NULL, 627, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14613891-L.jpg', '/works/OL37574011W', NULL, '2025', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'daughter-of-mine-megan-miranda', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:05', '2026-03-22 04:55:24');
