On the blood-soaked borders of Angland, Leo dan Brock struggles to win fame on the battlefield, and defeat the marauding armies of Stour Nightfall. He hopes for help from the crown. But King Jezal''s son, the feckless Prince Orso, is a man who specializes in disappointments.
 
Savine dan Glokta — socialite, investor, and daughter of the most feared man in the Union — plans to claw her way to the top of the slag-heap of society by any means necessary. But the slums boil over with a rage that all the money in the world cannot control.
 
The age of the machine dawns, but the age of magic refuses to die. With the help of the mad hillwoman Isern-i-Phail, Rikke struggles to control the blessing, or the curse, of the Long Eye. Glimpsing the future is one thing, but with the guiding hand of the First of the Magi still pulling the strings, changing it will be quite another . . .', 'In a fantasy world embracing industrial revolution, young protagonists navigate brutal wars, political intrigue, and personal vendettas amid societal upheaval.', 2014, '0316427624', '9780316427623', 496, NULL, 1220, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14543428-L.jpg', '/works/OL20131274W', NULL, 'Aug 08, 2019', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'a-little-hatred-joe-abercrombie', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:24', '2026-03-22 20:32:05');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c4de7cc6-c82d-4908-8280-0d2b73b9755e', 'Twice Magic', 'But now, the boy Wizard and girl Warrior have been brought together in the Badwoods and they have witnessed the shocking consequences of the Stone That Takes Away Magic. They will need to cast aside their differences once more--for an Evil Spell has broken free. It''s up to Xar and Wish to find the ingredients. But it means entering dangerous territory unannounced... Cressida Cowell brings her trademark wit to this spellbinding sequel, along with the stunning artwork and heartfelt adventure that has made her beloved around the world, weaving a story that is sure to transport readers to a world that will enchant and bewitch them.', 'A young wizard and warrior unite to battle evil magic in a land of witches and danger.', 2019, '6051735259', '9786051735252', 395, NULL, 336, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/11207961-L.jpg', '/works/OL19720761W', NULL, 'Oct 28, 2019', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'twice-magic-cressida-cowell', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:25', '2026-03-22 05:14:34');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('4b4b6b0f-61f6-49d7-b1bf-f033e86d8d82', 'The Hobbit', 'The Hobbit, or There and Back Again is a children''s fantasy novel by the English author J. R. R. Tolkien. It was published in 1937 to wide critical acclaim, being nominated for the Carnegie Medal and awarded a prize from the New York Herald Tribune for best juvenile fiction.', 'A hobbit embarks on an epic adventure with dwarves to reclaim treasure from a dragon, exploring themes of courage and greed.', 1937, NULL, NULL, 310, NULL, 624, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14624642-L.jpg', '/works/OL27482W', NULL, '1966', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'the-hobbit-jrr-tolkien', 1, 'google_books', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:25', '2026-03-22 03:54:11');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('1c34cd7c-b373-4cbc-bf12-15637c165980', 'Zanna''s Gift : A Life in Christmases', 'When the Pullman family lost their eldest son Ernie to an unexpected illness just before Christmas, 1938, it was devastating to all of them, but especially to young Suzanna, their four-year-old daughter who shared a special bond with her big brother. A strangely gifted child, Zanna loved to draw, but Ernie was the only one who was able to see the pictures in the curious patterns she made. And he did not live to see her last gift, a Christmas painting she had made just for him. This is the story of that gift, and how it inspired her and her whole family, generation to generation, to keep alive the spirit of imagination, hope, and love, for Christmases to come.', 'A heartfelt Christmas story of love and loss, following Zanna''s life through decades of family traditions.', 2009, NULL, '9781429990981', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '/works/OL38020255W', NULL, '2009', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'zannas-gift-a-life-in-christmases-orson-scott-card', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:25', '2026-03-22 03:22:28');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('b7820722-cdb1-48d3-80ff-68dc61d5955f', 'The Great Change', 'The Great Change (and Other Lies) is a novella-length collection that gathers four short stories related to Joe Abercrombie’s The Age of Madness, featuring old friends and new: from smugglers to kings, from diamond-cutters to dress-makers, from the most apparently insignificant of slaves to the most feared man in the Union, Old Sticks himself.', 'A novella collection of four short stories set in The Age of Madness, exploring themes of change and revolution in a grimdark fantasy world.', 2023, '1645240649', '9781645240648', 120, NULL, 1417, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14839818-L.jpg', '/works/OL42469606W', NULL, '2023-01-01', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'the-great-change-joe-abercrombie', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:27', '2026-03-22 05:06:07');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('d2dafdf7-08d0-4759-8728-fd7adad4039f', 'How to Seize a Dragon''s Jewel', 'In exile, and hunted by dragons and humans alike, can Hiccup the Viking find the dragon''s jewel and save the world from destruction?

The Dragon Rebellion has begun, bringing the Vikings'' darkest hour upon them. Hiccup has become an outcast, but that won''t stop him from going on the most harrowing and important quest of his life. He must find the Dragon''s Jewel. Book #10', 'Hiccup, in exile, must find the Dragon''s Jewel to save humanity in this dark, witty fantasy adventure.', 2013, '0316244090', '9780316244091', 388, NULL, 330, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/7845092-L.jpg', '/works/OL17571832W', NULL, '2013', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'how-to-seize-a-dragons-jewel-cressida-cowell', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:27', '2026-03-23 04:11:04');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('a01ece52-90dd-4a25-8b84-ec64e52ae021', 'War of Gifts', 'Orson Scott Card offers a Christmas gift to his millions of fans with A War of Gifts, a short novel set during Ender Wiggin''s first years at the Battle School where it is forbidden to celebrate religious holidays. The children come from many nations, many religions; while they are being trained for war, religious conflict between them is not on the curriculum.', 'A Christmas novella set in Ender''s Battle School, exploring religious conflict and tolerance among child soldiers.', 2009, NULL, '9781429940498', NULL, NULL, 120, NULL, '/works/OL38020595W', NULL, '2009', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'war-of-gifts-orson-scott-card', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:28', '2026-03-22 04:49:46');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('2cdcd7b4-dd2f-4a78-b6be-cf3cc01f895e', 'Before They Are Hanged', 'Superior Glokta has a problem. How do you defend a city surrounded by enemies and riddled with traitors, when your allies can by no means be trusted, and your predecessor vanished without a trace? It’s enough to make a torturer want to run – if he could even walk without a stick.

Northmen have spilled over the border of Angland and are spreading fire and death across the frozen country. Crown Prince Ladisla is poised to drive them back and win undying glory. There is only one problem – he commands the worst-armed, worst-trained, worst-led army in the world.

And Bayaz, the First of the Magi, is leading a party of bold adventurers on a perilous mission through the ruins of the past. The most hated woman in the South, the most feared man in the North, and the most selfish boy in the Union make a strange alliance, but a deadly one. They might even stand a chance of saving mankind from the Eaters. If they didn’t hate each other quite so much.

Ancient secrets will be uncovered. Bloody battles will be won and lost. Bitter enemies will be forgiven – but not before they are hanged.', 'Superior Glokta has a problem. How do you defend a city surrounded by enemies and riddled with traitors, when your allies can by no means be trusted, and your predecessor vanished...', 2007, '8411480739', '9788411480734', 560, NULL, 4500, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14595640-L.jpg', '/works/OL8400946W', NULL, 'Nov 24, 2022', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'before-they-are-hanged-joe-abercrombie', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:31:29', '2026-03-22 20:32:05');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('5d581f78-6a02-4151-8af6-50589168532e', 'There Is No Antimemetics Division', '(from back cover)

An antimeme is *an idea with self-censoring properties*; an idea which, by its intrinsic nature, discourages or prevents people from spreading it.

**Antimemes are real.** Think of any piece of information which you wouldn''t share with anybody, like passwords, taboos and dirty secrets. Or any piece of information which would be difficult to share even if you tried: complex equations, very boring passages of text, large blocks of random numbers, and dreams...

But anomalous antimemes are another matter entirely. How do you contain something you can''t record or remember? How do you fight a war against an enemy with effortless, perfect camouflage, when you can never even know that you''re at war?

Welcome to the Antimemetics Division.

